## .NET MAUI Theme Detection & Override

### Detect current theme

```csharp
AppTheme currentTheme = Application.Current.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified
```

### Subscribe to real-time changes

```csharp
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");

    // Update UI on main thread
    MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
    {
        ApplyTheme(newTheme);
    });
};
```

### Force a specific theme (override system setting)

```csharp
// Lock to dark mode regardless of system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Lock to light mode
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Light;

// Revert to following the system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

### Practical example — wiring it all together

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public App()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        RequestedThemeChanged += OnThemeChanged;
    }

    private void OnThemeChanged(object sender, AppThemeChangedEventArgs e)
    {
        Debug.WriteLine($"System theme → {e.RequestedTheme}");

        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            // Only apply if the user hasn't forced a theme
            if (UserAppTheme == AppTheme.Unspecified)
                ApplyTheme(e.RequestedTheme);
        });
    }

    private void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        Resources.MergedDictionaries.Clear();
        Resources.MergedDictionaries.Add(theme == AppTheme.Dark
            ? new DarkTheme()
            : new LightTheme());
    }
}
```

### XAML — reactive theme bindings (no code-behind needed)

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Black, Dark=White}" />

<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#FFFFFF, Dark=#1E1E1E}">
```

**Key points:**
- `RequestedTheme` — reads the OS setting (read-only).
- `UserAppTheme` — your app-level override (read/write). Set to `Unspecified` to follow the system again.
- `RequestedThemeChanged` fires only for **system** changes; setting `UserAppTheme` does not trigger it.
- `AppThemeBinding` in XAML reacts to both system and `UserAppTheme` changes automatically.
